

				gyr
				===
		

0.  Description.

	The GYR gadget consists of a layout of radio-boxes
	configured to resemble traffic-lights.

1.  Operation.

	See example below.

2.  zûdefine cx

	cx = target context of GYR
	z = `cx._GYR

	Define an GYR traffic-light system in cx.

3.  Variables

	_SHAPEû		rows,cols
	_LIGHT_i_jû	radio-box configured as a traffic-light
	_STATE[i;j]:	0, 1, or 2, depending on whether _LIGHT_i_j is
			  green, yellow, or red.
	_GEOMETRYû	`horizontal or `vertical
	_COLORSû	`red`gold`green
	_LIGHTSû	`r`y`g

	_FONTû		'courier-10'

	_GYR:		_SHAPEÒlayout of traffic-lights

4.  Restrictions

	`set callback on _STATE.
	shape of _STATE may not be changed.

5.  Example

		$load s
		$load gyr
		bûgyr.define `
		_SHAPEû5 6
		show b
		_SHAPEû3 4
		_GEOMETRYû`horizontal
		_STATE[]û3 4Ò0 1 2




